=== RAW MODEL ANSWER ===
Answer: Step 1: 4-bromobenzonitrile undergoes Pd-catalyzed cross-coupling with an n-butyl organometallic reagent (e.g., n-BuZnBr or n-BuB(OH)2) to give 4-butylbenzonitrile. | Step 2: Convert 4-butylbenzonitrile to the corresponding amidoxime, 4-butylbenzamidoxime, with NH2OH·HCl/base. | Step 3: Protect the phenol on the other aryl fragment as the anisole and use 3-chloro-4-methoxy-5-iodobenzoic acid; convert it to 3-chloro-4-methoxy-5-iodobenzoyl chloride with SOCl2 (or oxalyl chloride). | Step 4: Acylate 4-butylbenzamidoxime with 3-chloro-4-methoxy-5-iodobenzoyl chloride, then cyclodehydrate (e.g., POCl3 or heat) to form 3-(4-butylphenyl)-5-(3-chloro-4-methoxy-5-iodophenyl)-1,2,4-oxadiazole. | Step 5: Demethylate the anisole with BBr3 to give the target, CCCc1ccc(-c2nc(-c3cc(I)c(O)cc3Cl)no2)cc1.

=== NORMALIZED STUDENT ANSWER ===
